00:01:03.302 --> 00:01:04.760
and analyze your
user acquisitions.

00:01:07.400 --> 00:01:12.460
There are a ton of apps
available in the App

00:01:12.460 --> 00:01:14.710
and the Play Stores today.

00:01:14.710 --> 00:01:17.690
About a million-- actually,
more than a million

00:01:17.690 --> 00:01:20.370
apps in both of those locations.

00:01:20.370 --> 00:01:22.050
And if you think
about this, this

00:01:22.050 --> 00:01:24.790
presents an enormous challenge
to mobile app developers,

00:01:24.790 --> 00:01:25.290
right?

00:01:25.290 --> 00:01:26.831
You need to stand
out from the crowd.

00:01:26.831 --> 00:01:29.600
You need to get noticed.

00:01:29.600 --> 00:01:33.240
You need to drive
usage of your app.

00:01:33.240 --> 00:01:38.605
And the sheer volume of apps
out there is not the only hurdle

00:01:38.605 --> 00:01:41.620
that you face, but bringing
users into your app

00:01:41.620 --> 00:01:44.740
and engaging them time and time
again is another challenge.

00:01:44.740 --> 00:01:46.710
And you see the
other stat behind me,

00:01:46.710 --> 00:01:48.880
where literally
a quarter of apps

00:01:48.880 --> 00:01:52.680
are downloaded, installed
on users' phones,

00:01:52.680 --> 00:01:55.430
and yet never even run once.

00:01:55.430 --> 00:02:00.130
So there's a lot of
waste left in the system.

00:02:00.130 --> 00:02:04.480
Users are spending more and
more time in mobile apps.

00:02:04.480 --> 00:02:10.240
This is adding up to
over 30 hours per month

00:02:10.240 --> 00:02:12.567
being spent in
mobile applications.

00:02:12.567 --> 00:02:14.900
And what we're see thing is
it's some of this engagement

00:02:14.900 --> 00:02:18.760
is long periods of time
spent in game, but some of it

00:02:18.760 --> 00:02:22.424
is through tiny slices of
time that really add up.

00:02:22.424 --> 00:02:24.840
Users are pulling their mobile
phones out of their pockets

00:02:24.840 --> 00:02:27.560
to interact, to reach
for information,

00:02:27.560 --> 00:02:31.560
to make things happen even in
the real world, over 150 times

00:02:31.560 --> 00:02:32.560
a day.

00:02:32.560 --> 00:02:34.445
We think about these
as micro-moments.

00:02:34.445 --> 00:02:35.070
Think about it.

00:02:35.070 --> 00:02:36.653
You're standing at
the train platform.

00:02:36.653 --> 00:02:39.120
You're waiting for the next
commuter train to come.

00:02:39.120 --> 00:02:42.120
You pull out your phone, and
you start to work on a task.

00:02:42.120 --> 00:02:44.550
You start to work on something
that you needed to do.

00:02:44.550 --> 00:02:45.500
But then the train
comes, and you've

00:02:45.500 --> 00:02:46.940
got to get in, so you
kind of just, quick,

00:02:46.940 --> 00:02:48.940
shut down the phone, put
it back in your pocket,

00:02:48.940 --> 00:02:50.060
and climb in the train.

00:02:50.060 --> 00:02:52.060
When you get off, you
want to be able to pick up

00:02:52.060 --> 00:02:52.930
that task again.

00:02:52.930 --> 00:02:56.070
Your day is filled with all
of these slivers of moments

00:02:56.070 --> 00:02:59.104
where you can interact
with your mobile devices.

00:02:59.104 --> 00:02:59.770
Another example.

00:02:59.770 --> 00:03:01.630
You're waiting in line to
pick up a cup of coffee.

00:03:01.630 --> 00:03:03.504
You probably pull your
mobile phone back out,

00:03:03.504 --> 00:03:06.370
and you want to resume that
task where you left off.

00:03:06.370 --> 00:03:09.560
The reason mobile apps
work so well in this space

00:03:09.560 --> 00:03:12.350
is that they don't have to
worry about connectivity.

00:03:12.350 --> 00:03:14.280
They can save state,
they can provide you

00:03:14.280 --> 00:03:16.830
with clean rich UIs,
and they're right there

00:03:16.830 --> 00:03:19.180
to be accessed on
your home screen.

00:03:19.180 --> 00:03:20.520
So all this time adds up.

00:03:20.520 --> 00:03:23.350
And it adds up to now
over 30 hours per month

00:03:23.350 --> 00:03:26.430
spent in mobile applications.

00:03:26.430 --> 00:03:30.220
And users are using more and
more mobile apps over time.

00:03:30.220 --> 00:03:31.790
In fact, the latest
stat indicates

00:03:31.790 --> 00:03:36.430
that 36 is the number of apps
that the average American has

00:03:36.430 --> 00:03:38.920
on her cell phone.

00:03:38.920 --> 00:03:42.620
And, as I mentioned a few
moments ago, a quarter of those

00:03:42.620 --> 00:03:43.990
are left completely unused.

00:03:46.580 --> 00:03:48.820
We've been out
talking to friends,

00:03:48.820 --> 00:03:51.450
talking to users
around the globe,

00:03:51.450 --> 00:03:53.550
really trying to
understand more about how

00:03:53.550 --> 00:03:55.692
folks are fitting apps
into their daily life.

00:03:55.692 --> 00:03:57.900
And I'd like to take you
through one of these stories

00:03:57.900 --> 00:04:01.882
to sort of illustrate the
power of mobile applications.

00:04:01.882 --> 00:04:03.215
So this is our friend Christian.

00:04:03.215 --> 00:04:04.610
This is a true story.

00:04:04.610 --> 00:04:06.280
Christian is a
young professional.

00:04:06.280 --> 00:04:07.860
He lives in Philadelphia.

00:04:07.860 --> 00:04:09.309
And he has a younger brother.

00:04:09.309 --> 00:04:11.350
And his younger brother
recently started running.

00:04:14.570 --> 00:04:17.950
As with most sibling
relationships,

00:04:17.950 --> 00:04:20.550
they have a bit of
a sibling rivalry,

00:04:20.550 --> 00:04:23.810
and so Christian is very eager
to go running with his brother

00:04:23.810 --> 00:04:26.860
as well and show him that
he can do him one better.

00:04:26.860 --> 00:04:30.470
So 5:00 AM, Christian's brother
shows up at Christian's house.

00:04:30.470 --> 00:04:32.440
Sounds like about the
time my kids wake up,

00:04:32.440 --> 00:04:34.023
which is a little
early to be running.

00:04:34.023 --> 00:04:36.250
But anyway, his brother
shows up at the house,

00:04:36.250 --> 00:04:38.041
and his brother pulls
out his mobile phone,

00:04:38.041 --> 00:04:40.260
and he starts configuring
his running app.

00:04:40.260 --> 00:04:42.660
He's downloaded a running
app that helps coaching him,

00:04:42.660 --> 00:04:45.402
driving him to be a
better and better runner.

00:04:45.402 --> 00:04:46.860
And Christian
thinks, well, dammit,

00:04:46.860 --> 00:04:48.318
I can't be one-upped
by my brother.

00:04:48.318 --> 00:04:49.870
So he pulls out
his mobile phone,

00:04:49.870 --> 00:04:53.230
and he wants his
own running app.

00:04:53.230 --> 00:04:55.350
But Christian isn't going
to sit there and use

00:04:55.350 --> 00:04:57.060
the same running
app as his brother.

00:04:57.060 --> 00:04:59.070
He's unique, he's
his own person,

00:04:59.070 --> 00:05:02.060
and because it's a
rivalry, he does a search,

00:05:02.060 --> 00:05:05.270
and he starts looking for
the right kind of running app

00:05:05.270 --> 00:05:07.610
for him.

00:05:07.610 --> 00:05:09.940
He finds a site with
the top 10 running apps,

00:05:09.940 --> 00:05:11.110
and he peruses them.

00:05:11.110 --> 00:05:14.690
And he finds that there's
this Nike+ running app,

00:05:14.690 --> 00:05:17.950
which really,
really sings to him,

00:05:17.950 --> 00:05:20.720
because he's always been
an avid Nike customer.

00:05:20.720 --> 00:05:22.870
And he has one of those
pairs of Nike sneakers

00:05:22.870 --> 00:05:25.090
that have the
little chips in them

00:05:25.090 --> 00:05:28.120
so they can actually track
his pacing and running.

00:05:28.120 --> 00:05:31.400
And this happens every day.

00:05:31.400 --> 00:05:34.160
Thousands upon
thousands of times.

00:05:34.160 --> 00:05:39.700
Users need an application to
service some need for them.

00:05:39.700 --> 00:05:41.990
They have to make almost
a split second decision

00:05:41.990 --> 00:05:43.700
with a little bit
of information.

00:05:43.700 --> 00:05:46.660
But for Christian,
this app has now

00:05:46.660 --> 00:05:48.160
become an integral
part of his life.

00:05:48.160 --> 00:05:49.750
It sits there on
his home screen,

00:05:49.750 --> 00:05:51.750
and he uses it every day.

00:05:51.750 --> 00:05:55.090
Think about the power of the
connection that was just built

00:05:55.090 --> 00:05:58.580
between Nike and Christian.

00:05:58.580 --> 00:06:01.010
Discoverability is the
first of these challenges.

00:06:01.010 --> 00:06:02.930
How do you get your
app to really stand out

00:06:02.930 --> 00:06:04.730
from the crowd?

00:06:04.730 --> 00:06:10.150
And today, as app developers,
you're doing a lot of work.

00:06:10.150 --> 00:06:12.440
You're worrying about
optimizing your listings.

00:06:12.440 --> 00:06:14.700
You've got to create
beautiful videos,

00:06:14.700 --> 00:06:16.325
get them out there,
get them published,

00:06:16.325 --> 00:06:18.170
get users to watch them.

00:06:18.170 --> 00:06:20.260
You probably want to
optimize your keywords

00:06:20.260 --> 00:06:22.790
so that you can easily be
found in searches on these Play

00:06:22.790 --> 00:06:23.720
stores.

00:06:23.720 --> 00:06:26.800
Many of you realize that you
should also extend your reach

00:06:26.800 --> 00:06:30.754
by paying for app promotion.

00:06:30.754 --> 00:06:32.170
And then you
probably have to deal

00:06:32.170 --> 00:06:35.620
with a variety of
social channels.

00:06:35.620 --> 00:06:38.500
This is an awful lot of
work, and at Google we're

00:06:38.500 --> 00:06:41.070
really leaning in to make
this as easy as possible,

00:06:41.070 --> 00:06:45.000
to really cut through as much
of this as we can for you.

00:06:45.000 --> 00:06:46.860
So let's talk a little
bit about the assets

00:06:46.860 --> 00:06:50.620
that Google has to bear
to bring to the solution

00:06:50.620 --> 00:06:55.740
to really facilitate app
discovery for all of you.

00:06:55.740 --> 00:06:58.400
It really comes down
to the fact that we

00:06:58.400 --> 00:07:02.470
have a large variety,
a heterogeneous set,

00:07:02.470 --> 00:07:05.840
of different properties
and platforms

00:07:05.840 --> 00:07:09.150
that users are interacting
with on a daily basis--

00:07:09.150 --> 00:07:11.210
on a minutely basis.

00:07:11.210 --> 00:07:14.490
And so across Search, and
the Play Store, and the AdMob

00:07:14.490 --> 00:07:18.290
in-app network,
and YouTube, we can

00:07:18.290 --> 00:07:21.700
help users connect
with apps as they're

00:07:21.700 --> 00:07:23.980
going about their daily life.

00:07:23.980 --> 00:07:26.830
And we're working on a
whole variety of tools

00:07:26.830 --> 00:07:30.580
to help you connect with
users at the right moments,

00:07:30.580 --> 00:07:32.510
as they're looking
for these solutions

00:07:32.510 --> 00:07:35.830
to install on their phone.

00:07:35.830 --> 00:07:38.590
We understand that,
for app developers,

00:07:38.590 --> 00:07:41.034
it is not an Android-only world.

00:07:41.034 --> 00:07:43.700
And I want to make sure that all
of you understand this as well.

00:07:43.700 --> 00:07:46.160
From our perspective,
we are absolutely

00:07:46.160 --> 00:07:48.400
committed to bringing
these solutions

00:07:48.400 --> 00:07:54.310
to life across platforms,
across both iOS and AdMob.

00:07:54.310 --> 00:07:56.080
Because, for all
of you, you need

00:07:56.080 --> 00:07:58.300
to grow the largest
audience possible.

00:07:58.300 --> 00:08:00.120
And if we limit to
one platform, you're

00:08:00.120 --> 00:08:01.570
not going to be able to do this.

00:08:01.570 --> 00:08:03.440
This is an ongoing
commitment for everything

00:08:03.440 --> 00:08:07.690
that we're doing in
this mobile apps space.

00:08:07.690 --> 00:08:09.730
Now I'd like to welcome
Scott Huffman come up

00:08:09.730 --> 00:08:11.790
on stage to talk us
through what we're

00:08:11.790 --> 00:08:13.690
doing on the organic
side of the world,

00:08:13.690 --> 00:08:17.530
to really help with
discovery and engagement.

00:08:17.530 --> 00:08:21.102
SCOTT HUFFMAN: Thanks, Jonathan.

00:08:21.102 --> 00:08:21.895
Hi, everyone.

00:08:21.895 --> 00:08:23.700
I'm Scott, and I'm
one of the leads

00:08:23.700 --> 00:08:25.770
in the search team at Google.

00:08:25.770 --> 00:08:29.220
And, in particular, I have
the really fantastic job

00:08:29.220 --> 00:08:31.419
of leading up our
mobile search efforts.

00:08:31.419 --> 00:08:32.919
And over the last
couple years we've

00:08:32.919 --> 00:08:36.320
been very focused
on how can we take

00:08:36.320 --> 00:08:39.740
the great content and the
great services that all of you

00:08:39.740 --> 00:08:42.620
are creating your apps and
make those a first order

00:08:42.620 --> 00:08:44.745
part of the Google Search
experience for our users?

00:08:47.380 --> 00:08:51.050
Now, Jonathan talked about
the hard, hard problems

00:08:51.050 --> 00:08:55.040
that I think all of you
face in this apps world.

00:08:55.040 --> 00:08:57.370
First of all, out
of all those million

00:08:57.370 --> 00:08:59.320
apps that are out
there how in the world

00:08:59.320 --> 00:09:02.539
do users find out about your
app when they have a need,

00:09:02.539 --> 00:09:04.080
understand that your
app is something

00:09:04.080 --> 00:09:05.920
they can meet their
need, and decide

00:09:05.920 --> 00:09:08.230
to put that app on their phone?

00:09:08.230 --> 00:09:10.055
Even once you get
through that hurdle,

00:09:10.055 --> 00:09:12.430
we all understand-- and Jonathan
gave some of the stats--

00:09:12.430 --> 00:09:14.660
that you're not done
yet, because users

00:09:14.660 --> 00:09:16.110
forget your app is there.

00:09:16.110 --> 00:09:18.160
They don't really
understand all the things

00:09:18.160 --> 00:09:20.090
that your app can do for them.

00:09:20.090 --> 00:09:21.960
And a lot of times
it sits unused.

00:09:21.960 --> 00:09:25.400
So how do you get users to
reengage once the app is there?

00:09:25.400 --> 00:09:27.675
Now, for us and Google
and the Search team,

00:09:27.675 --> 00:09:31.240
this actually sounds like
kind of a familiar problem.

00:09:31.240 --> 00:09:33.120
We've seen this one before.

00:09:33.120 --> 00:09:36.630
If we go back in time, way
back to ancient history,

00:09:36.630 --> 00:09:41.500
in 1998, here is a graph
of the number of websites

00:09:41.500 --> 00:09:42.670
that were out there.

00:09:42.670 --> 00:09:45.535
And there were about a
million websites in 1998.

00:09:45.535 --> 00:09:47.160
Lots of great things,
obviously-- there

00:09:47.160 --> 00:09:49.910
was huge growth to lead
to this million websites.

00:09:49.910 --> 00:09:52.790
But if you were creating
a new web application,

00:09:52.790 --> 00:09:56.000
it was very, very difficult
for you to get discovered.

00:09:56.000 --> 00:10:00.171
Say that you had a fantastic
collection of cookie recipes,

00:10:00.171 --> 00:10:01.420
and you wanted to put that up.

00:10:01.420 --> 00:10:02.836
And, in particular,
maybe you just

00:10:02.836 --> 00:10:06.230
have the most fantastic
chocolate chip cookie recipes.

00:10:06.230 --> 00:10:08.590
How in the world would
people find your site?

00:10:08.590 --> 00:10:11.230
You could put yourself
into web directories,

00:10:11.230 --> 00:10:13.457
you could try word
of mouth, and really

00:10:13.457 --> 00:10:15.040
trying to generate
some buzz, but it's

00:10:15.040 --> 00:10:18.910
very difficult for a user who
says to themselves, "I really

00:10:18.910 --> 00:10:22.000
need an organic chocolate
chip cookie recipe to bake,"

00:10:22.000 --> 00:10:24.180
to find you.

00:10:24.180 --> 00:10:27.880
And then along came Google
and other search technologies,

00:10:27.880 --> 00:10:30.360
and it really changed the
equation pretty dramatically,

00:10:30.360 --> 00:10:32.639
where now all of
a sudden users who

00:10:32.639 --> 00:10:35.180
needed that organic chocolate
chip cookie recipe-- that's not

00:10:35.180 --> 00:10:39.690
very easy to say, by the way--
could put that into the box,

00:10:39.690 --> 00:10:44.130
and if your site had the
relevant best chocolate chip

00:10:44.130 --> 00:10:46.380
cookie recipes out
there, it would come up,

00:10:46.380 --> 00:10:50.350
users would discover it,
and as users used that, it

00:10:50.350 --> 00:10:51.820
would come up more and more.

00:10:51.820 --> 00:10:56.930
And so we saw an explosion where
we went from a million websites

00:10:56.930 --> 00:11:00.980
to over a billion websites with
just even more dramatic growth

00:11:00.980 --> 00:11:04.170
because it enabled the
long tail of everyone who

00:11:04.170 --> 00:11:06.500
wanted to create content
services on the web

00:11:06.500 --> 00:11:10.250
to be discovered, not
just in a directory,

00:11:10.250 --> 00:11:13.230
but in a needs-based way
where users could find you

00:11:13.230 --> 00:11:16.480
by expressing their need.

