in fact what we're
seeing at Google

00:12:00.650 --> 00:12:03.690
is that mobile users are
in fact coming to Google

00:12:03.690 --> 00:12:08.040
search expressing needs many,
many millions of times a day.

00:12:08.040 --> 00:12:11.130
And we're seeing
incredible growth in that.

00:12:11.130 --> 00:12:14.910
So here's just one stat that
shows that-- that more Google

00:12:14.910 --> 00:12:17.930
searches now are taking
place on mobile phones

00:12:17.930 --> 00:12:21.070
than on laptop and desktop
computers in places like the US

00:12:21.070 --> 00:12:23.400
and Japan and many
other countries.

00:12:23.400 --> 00:12:24.840
And this is just accelerating.

00:12:24.840 --> 00:12:28.010
Users don't just tap on app
icons; they come to Google

00:12:28.010 --> 00:12:29.590
and they express a need.

00:12:29.590 --> 00:12:32.850
And we want to bring your apps
to them when they do that.

00:12:32.850 --> 00:12:35.030
Now, our solution
to this problem,

00:12:35.030 --> 00:12:36.940
and the way you could
tap into Google Search,

00:12:36.940 --> 00:12:39.195
is something that we
call app indexing.

00:12:39.195 --> 00:12:42.350
And app indexing is
a pretty simple idea.

00:12:42.350 --> 00:12:46.820
What you do is, basically,
you change your app

00:12:46.820 --> 00:12:48.860
to add deep linking capability.

00:12:48.860 --> 00:12:51.720
Deep links are
basically URLs or URIs

00:12:51.720 --> 00:12:55.500
that point to each of the
different pieces of content

00:12:55.500 --> 00:12:58.600
or individual services
inside of your app.

00:12:58.600 --> 00:13:01.630
And we have a lot of help
here at the conference

00:13:01.630 --> 00:13:03.730
and online to help you do that.

00:13:03.730 --> 00:13:06.570
We have folks giving
box talks-- in fact,

00:13:06.570 --> 00:13:08.260
there's one right
after this talk--

00:13:08.260 --> 00:13:11.590
that goes into kind of the nuts
and bolts of how you do this.

00:13:11.590 --> 00:13:15.870
We have folks kind of manning a
help desk out here, and so on.

00:13:15.870 --> 00:13:18.144
After you add deep
links to your app.

00:13:18.144 --> 00:13:19.560
There are a few
simple choices you

00:13:19.560 --> 00:13:23.390
have for publishing your
app's deep links to Google.

00:13:23.390 --> 00:13:26.710
And then, on the Google side, we
do basically what we always do.

00:13:26.710 --> 00:13:30.350
We take those deep links and
we add that to our index,

00:13:30.350 --> 00:13:34.290
so that our index now not only
contains content and services

00:13:34.290 --> 00:13:36.940
from the web, but
also from your app.

00:13:36.940 --> 00:13:39.810
And then we apply our
set of ranking algorithms

00:13:39.810 --> 00:13:42.440
to surface your app,
and in particular

00:13:42.440 --> 00:13:44.340
the individual pieces
inside of your apps

00:13:44.340 --> 00:13:47.200
that are most relevant
for a user's query

00:13:47.200 --> 00:13:50.660
when users come along
with those needs.

00:13:50.660 --> 00:13:52.760
Now, even before any
of this app indexing

00:13:52.760 --> 00:13:56.070
stuff, of course, if people
come to Google Search and ask

00:13:56.070 --> 00:13:59.190
for apps, we're going to give
them the best apps of the kind

00:13:59.190 --> 00:14:00.040
that they ask for.

00:14:00.040 --> 00:14:02.030
So, for example, if a
user comes along and asks

00:14:02.030 --> 00:14:04.460
for cooking apps,
Google Search is

00:14:04.460 --> 00:14:07.504
going to bring up a nice list of
some of the best cooking apps.

00:14:07.504 --> 00:14:09.670
This is something that we've
been doing for a while,

00:14:09.670 --> 00:14:11.169
and one thing people
may not realize

00:14:11.169 --> 00:14:15.360
is that, in fact, there is a
fair amount of app installation

00:14:15.360 --> 00:14:18.060
that flows through
the Google search box,

00:14:18.060 --> 00:14:21.100
in addition to what's coming
through the Play Store.

00:14:21.100 --> 00:14:22.710
But more often,
people come to Google

00:14:22.710 --> 00:14:25.110
and they ask for
things that they need.

00:14:25.110 --> 00:14:26.610
They don't know if
they need an app,

00:14:26.610 --> 00:14:30.390
they just know that they need
animal-shaped cookie ideas.

00:14:30.390 --> 00:14:33.290
And who hasn't needed that?

00:14:33.290 --> 00:14:36.670
And what happens if
the user, for example,

00:14:36.670 --> 00:14:39.500
doesn't have the
Pinterest app today?

00:14:39.500 --> 00:14:42.690
Starting from this side,
if the user says to Google

00:14:42.690 --> 00:14:45.310
"animal-shaped cookie ideas,"
in addition to content from

00:14:45.310 --> 00:14:49.620
the web and other apps, Google
actually offers an installation

00:14:49.620 --> 00:14:52.900
offer for apps that have
great content about that.

00:14:52.900 --> 00:14:54.380
In this case, one
of the apps that

00:14:54.380 --> 00:14:56.910
has great content about the
animal-shaped cookie ideas

00:14:56.910 --> 00:14:58.540
is the Pinterest app.

00:14:58.540 --> 00:15:00.790
Once a user taps
that install button,

00:15:00.790 --> 00:15:02.990
they go through the
Play Store install flow,

00:15:02.990 --> 00:15:04.640
and when the app
is installed, you

00:15:04.640 --> 00:15:08.390
can see in the middle screen
here not just an open button,

00:15:08.390 --> 00:15:10.850
but that green continue button.

00:15:10.850 --> 00:15:13.380
And when the user taps
on that continue button,

00:15:13.380 --> 00:15:17.150
it in fact takes them not just
to the top of the Pinterest

00:15:17.150 --> 00:15:19.750
app, but straight into the
content that they asked for.

00:15:19.750 --> 00:15:24.400
In this case, a lovely page full
of animal-shaped cookie ideas.

00:15:24.400 --> 00:15:25.900
And so the user has
gone all the way

00:15:25.900 --> 00:15:29.484
through from discovering
the app installing the album

00:15:29.484 --> 00:15:31.400
and then getting to the
content that they were

00:15:31.400 --> 00:15:33.780
looking for inside of that.

00:15:33.780 --> 00:15:35.950
Now once your app is
installed, then you

00:15:35.950 --> 00:15:38.510
can drive re-engagement
through those deep links

00:15:38.510 --> 00:15:40.580
that you've provided to Google.

00:15:40.580 --> 00:15:42.660
And whether users are
looking, in these examples,

00:15:42.660 --> 00:15:46.490
for things like a restaurant,
a craft idea, a movie, or any

00:15:46.490 --> 00:15:49.640
of the other zillion things that
people come to Google every day

00:15:49.640 --> 00:15:53.540
to search for-- if your
app has relevant content,

00:15:53.540 --> 00:15:57.590
and it is ranked in the
list here, it'll come up.

00:15:57.590 --> 00:16:02.980
So you see here some restaurant
related apps, the Etsy craft

00:16:02.980 --> 00:16:06.110
app, some movie related
apps, and so on,

00:16:06.110 --> 00:16:09.022
that allow users, by
expressing their need,

00:16:09.022 --> 00:16:10.730
to come back to your
app again and again.

00:16:13.760 --> 00:16:16.280
Now probably people have
heard-- because we've

00:16:16.280 --> 00:16:18.300
talked about it a lot
over time-- that Google

00:16:18.300 --> 00:16:22.440
uses hundreds of signals
that come together to drive

00:16:22.440 --> 00:16:24.900
our ranking algorithms.

00:16:24.900 --> 00:16:27.790
And by making your app
content available-- visible,

00:16:27.790 --> 00:16:32.220
basically-- to Google, that
content and the characteristics

00:16:32.220 --> 00:16:35.770
of your app are able to
influence the ranking

00:16:35.770 --> 00:16:38.990
and to help users find that
app at the appropriate times.

00:16:41.780 --> 00:16:43.220
Now, that all sounds great.

00:16:43.220 --> 00:16:45.080
Or at least I'm hoping
it sounds great,

00:16:45.080 --> 00:16:47.680
because I'm trying to give you
the best sales pitch for app

00:16:47.680 --> 00:16:49.420
indexing that I can.

00:16:49.420 --> 00:16:52.100
But how do we know that
any of this stuff works?

00:16:52.100 --> 00:16:54.760
One tool that we have
is something that's

00:16:54.760 --> 00:16:56.360
called the search console.

00:16:56.360 --> 00:17:00.910
And back in the day, back
in my 1998-type graph,

00:17:00.910 --> 00:17:03.540
this tool-- and actually,
more recently than that,

00:17:03.540 --> 00:17:05.990
the tool was called
Webmaster Tools.

00:17:05.990 --> 00:17:10.750
In fact we've not only renamed
it Search Console to get away

00:17:10.750 --> 00:17:12.790
from the idea that is
just for webmasters,

00:17:12.790 --> 00:17:15.569
but also added a lot of
tools that are really

00:17:15.569 --> 00:17:19.310
focused on apps, so that both
webmasters and app developers

00:17:19.310 --> 00:17:22.119
can come to the search console
and get a really nice picture,

00:17:22.119 --> 00:17:24.551
analytically, of what's
happening with your app

00:17:24.551 --> 00:17:26.800
from the point of view of
Google Search-- what traffic

00:17:26.800 --> 00:17:29.699
is flowing from Google
that's coming into your app.

00:17:29.699 --> 00:17:31.240
And let's look at
some of the results

00:17:31.240 --> 00:17:33.790
that some of our
partners are seeing.

00:17:33.790 --> 00:17:37.620
Now, it's early days, but these
are kind of some early results,

00:17:37.620 --> 00:17:40.530
but really exciting
for our app partners.

00:17:40.530 --> 00:17:42.472
The Guardian--
what they're seeing

00:17:42.472 --> 00:17:44.805
is that, for users that have
the Guardian app installed,

00:17:44.805 --> 00:17:47.710
and that therefore are
seeing app links in Google

00:17:47.710 --> 00:17:50.080
Search instead of
web links, they're

00:17:50.080 --> 00:17:53.830
seeing a significant increase in
the clickthrough of those users

00:17:53.830 --> 00:17:56.711
to go into the app, as opposed
to users to select the Guardian

00:17:56.711 --> 00:17:57.210
website.

00:17:57.210 --> 00:18:00.420
So a 4.5% jump of
that backclick.

00:18:00.420 --> 00:18:03.220
So a nice increase
in reengagement.

00:18:03.220 --> 00:18:07.060
Etsy, they've seen increased
traffic from referrals,

00:18:07.060 --> 00:18:11.550
things that are flowing through
Google to them, of over 11%.

00:18:11.550 --> 00:18:15.430
And Tabelog, who is a
Japanese restaurant app,

00:18:15.430 --> 00:18:17.900
is seeing increased app traffic
to their restaurant pages,

00:18:17.900 --> 00:18:19.860
so kind of the
core content pages,

00:18:19.860 --> 00:18:22.780
the core purpose of
their app, of almost 10%.

00:18:22.780 --> 00:18:24.470
So, again, early
days, but pretty

00:18:24.470 --> 00:18:28.360
nice results for something
that's completely free

00:18:28.360 --> 00:18:32.820
and that is easy for apps to do.

00:18:32.820 --> 00:18:34.394
So where are we
going with all this?

00:18:34.394 --> 00:18:36.810
Well, Jonathan mentioned that
cross-platform is incredibly

00:18:36.810 --> 00:18:38.200
important for us at Google.

00:18:38.200 --> 00:18:40.350
We understand that
your app needs

00:18:40.350 --> 00:18:42.780
to work across these
different platforms.

00:18:42.780 --> 00:18:45.620
And so we actually announced--
I think it was on Wednesday--

00:18:45.620 --> 00:18:49.640
and began rolling out our
iOS approach to, or solution

00:18:49.640 --> 00:18:51.260
for, app indexing.

00:18:51.260 --> 00:18:54.230
And on iOS we've started
sort of the same way

00:18:54.230 --> 00:18:56.280
we started on Android,
which is we worked

00:18:56.280 --> 00:18:59.400
with a great set of partners--
you see their icons here--

00:18:59.400 --> 00:19:01.860
to do the initial launch.

00:19:01.860 --> 00:19:03.980
And we're just kind of
checking that, making sure

00:19:03.980 --> 00:19:06.600
all the pipes are running
smoothly, and so on.

00:19:06.600 --> 00:19:12.930
And then we'll open this up
to everyone in not very long.

00:19:12.930 --> 00:19:14.800
I'm also very happy
to announce today

00:19:14.800 --> 00:19:17.560
that we are opening
up app indexing

00:19:17.560 --> 00:19:22.100
two apps that only exist as
apps and not as websites.

00:19:22.100 --> 00:19:23.920
So far, what we've
done is really

00:19:23.920 --> 00:19:27.642
work on it with apps that have
a corresponding web presence.

00:19:27.642 --> 00:19:29.600
But there are a lot of
great apps in the world,

00:19:29.600 --> 00:19:31.058
and probably many
of you are making

00:19:31.058 --> 00:19:32.879
them, that don't have
corresponding web

00:19:32.879 --> 00:19:34.795
presence, that still
provide wonderful content

00:19:34.795 --> 00:19:36.580
and services for our users.

00:19:36.580 --> 00:19:40.110
What this project
allows us to do

00:19:40.110 --> 00:19:42.090
is bring those apps
into our index as well.

00:19:42.090 --> 00:19:45.360
So things like HotelTonight,
Visual Anatomy Free,

00:19:45.360 --> 00:19:48.560
and several others are kind
of our initial partners here.

00:19:48.560 --> 00:19:51.540
Here we're going to be launching
this initial set of partners,

00:19:51.540 --> 00:19:53.966
again, just to get
the pipes cleaned out

00:19:53.966 --> 00:19:55.590
and make sure that
everything's working

00:19:55.590 --> 00:19:58.010
within the next few weeks,
and then later in the year

00:19:58.010 --> 00:19:59.632
we'll open this up for everyone.

00:19:59.632 --> 00:20:01.090
And we're really
excited about this

00:20:01.090 --> 00:20:02.589
because we think
it really will open

00:20:02.589 --> 00:20:05.630
the floodgates to
letting any app be

00:20:05.630 --> 00:20:09.440
a part of Google's index.

00:20:09.440 --> 00:20:13.360
So hopefully I've convinced you
that a great way for your app

00:20:13.360 --> 00:20:16.810
to get to be discovered
and reengaged with users

00:20:16.810 --> 00:20:20.340
is through Google Search and
through indexing your app.

00:20:20.340 --> 00:20:23.730
Allowing users to come to
Google and express a need

00:20:23.730 --> 00:20:25.970
to find the great content
and the great service

00:20:25.970 --> 00:20:28.190
inside your app.

00:20:28.190 --> 00:20:29.790
We're seeing a lot
of effectiveness

00:20:29.790 --> 00:20:31.190
here for app developers.

00:20:31.190 --> 00:20:33.990
It's completely free, and if
you want to learn more about it,

00:20:33.990 --> 00:20:36.850
you see the link here with
lots of documentation,

00:20:36.850 --> 00:20:38.972
and also the box talk that
comes right after this.

00:20:38.972 --> 00:20:40.930
Thanks very much, and
I'll bring back Jonathan.

00:20:44.350 --> 00:20:46.940
JONATHAN ALFERNESS:
Thanks, Scott.

00:20:46.940 --> 00:20:49.050
Thanks, Scott.

00:20:49.050 --> 00:20:51.580
It's incredible to
see all of this work

00:20:51.580 --> 00:20:54.960
that Scott and his team are
doing to really bring apps

00:20:54.960 --> 00:20:57.750
to life within the core of
what Google has to offer

00:20:57.750 --> 00:21:00.030
the world-- our search product.

00:21:00.030 --> 00:21:01.950
Seeing apps as first
class citizens,

00:21:01.950 --> 00:21:03.870
and searching all of
this great deep linking

00:21:03.870 --> 00:21:06.590
technology across
both platforms,

00:21:06.590 --> 00:21:08.690
brings the biggest
smile to my face,

00:21:08.690 --> 00:21:11.010
because it just shows
this commitment.

00:21:11.010 --> 00:21:12.710
And it shows how
much more we're going

00:21:12.710 --> 00:21:14.490
to be able to do in
this mobile world

00:21:14.490 --> 00:21:17.450
when we really combined
the great power that Google

00:21:17.450 --> 00:21:19.840
Search has to offer with
this wonderful content

00:21:19.840 --> 00:21:24.199
that you guys are all creating
in these millions of apps.

00:21:24.199 --> 00:21:25.240
We're going to pivot now.

00:21:25.240 --> 00:21:27.670
We're going to
spend the last 10,

00:21:27.670 --> 00:21:30.195
15 minutes or so talking
about paid advertising

00:21:30.195 --> 00:21:31.820
and talking about
some of the solutions

00:21:31.820 --> 00:21:34.070
that Google is
bringing to the front.

00:21:34.070 --> 00:21:37.800
It's really aimed at making
it easier for all of you

00:21:37.800 --> 00:21:40.590
from an advertising standpoint
to reach those users, to reach

00:21:40.590 --> 00:21:44.070
them effectively, to reach the
high value users that you need

00:21:44.070 --> 00:21:47.030
to, and to automate that
as much as possible,

00:21:47.030 --> 00:21:49.910
bringing them into your app.

00:21:49.910 --> 00:21:55.990
Scott's history about
Google, about the work

00:21:55.990 --> 00:21:59.380
that we did to really bring
websites to life, web search

00:21:59.380 --> 00:22:03.320
to life, is an analogy that
I want to draw on as well.

00:22:03.320 --> 00:22:07.310
Because, if we think
about paid ads at Google,

00:22:07.310 --> 00:22:09.840
we've generally
followed along with what

00:22:09.840 --> 00:22:12.580
our friends on the
organic side have done.

00:22:12.580 --> 00:22:16.580
Yes, we do have our usual
church and state policies,

00:22:16.580 --> 00:22:19.300
but we've tried to
make the ads that we

00:22:19.300 --> 00:22:22.410
show to users as
native, as integrated

00:22:22.410 --> 00:22:24.430
in our experience as possible.

00:22:24.430 --> 00:22:27.900
If you go all the way
back to 2002, 2003,

00:22:27.900 --> 00:22:30.770
this was the very
inception of AdWords,

00:22:30.770 --> 00:22:34.454
of Search ads on Google.

00:22:34.454 --> 00:22:36.370
And we're doing the same
thing here with apps.

00:22:36.370 --> 00:22:38.990
We're essentially
following that history

00:22:38.990 --> 00:22:40.300
and following that path.

00:22:40.300 --> 00:22:42.800
And we're using a
lot of the lessons

00:22:42.800 --> 00:22:44.850
that we've learned
over the last 15 years

00:22:44.850 --> 00:22:47.900
to bring app
advertising to Google

00:22:47.900 --> 00:22:52.480
in much the same way that we
brought website advertising.

00:22:52.480 --> 00:22:54.770
This brings me to
app install ads.

00:22:54.770 --> 00:22:58.610
So we have app install ads as
an offering today across just

00:22:58.610 --> 00:23:00.250
about all of our channels.

00:23:00.250 --> 00:23:05.670
Between Search, Display,
YouTube, in-app.

00:23:05.670 --> 00:23:07.820
And we try to make it as
easy as possible for you

00:23:07.820 --> 00:23:10.480
guys to create these creatives,
to get them distributed,

00:23:10.480 --> 00:23:12.190
to get these ads
targeted and put

00:23:12.190 --> 00:23:14.130
in front of the eyeballs
of the right users,

00:23:14.130 --> 00:23:17.580
so that you're driving
high-value lifetime

00:23:17.580 --> 00:23:21.170
users to your application.

00:23:21.170 --> 00:23:22.920
Perhaps the most
exciting announcement

00:23:22.920 --> 00:23:25.570
that we've made in this
space over the last-- well,

00:23:25.570 --> 00:23:29.720
I think since we even got
started in app advertising,

00:23:29.720 --> 00:23:33.280
is the fact that we are now in
the process of bringing ads,

00:23:33.280 --> 00:23:36.970
Search ads, to the Play Store.

00:23:36.970 --> 00:23:40.300
We've currently been running
a beta, an early pilot,

00:23:40.300 --> 00:23:42.422
with a number of advertisers.

00:23:42.422 --> 00:23:43.630
This is going extremely well.

00:23:43.630 --> 00:23:45.260
If you think about
it, the Play Store

00:23:45.260 --> 00:23:48.580
captures the very
moment of intent

00:23:48.580 --> 00:23:52.830
when a user knows that she needs
a certain mobile application

00:23:52.830 --> 00:23:55.990
to solve a problem, the
task that she has laid out

00:23:55.990 --> 00:23:57.330
before her.

00:23:57.330 --> 00:24:00.310
And you see a couple
of examples here.

00:24:00.310 --> 00:24:04.620
When this launches, we will
show at most one ad at the top.

00:24:04.620 --> 00:24:08.267
It will be clearly labeled
as such, as we always have.

00:24:08.267 --> 00:24:09.850
And, again, we're
seeing great results

00:24:09.850 --> 00:24:11.560
both for users and
advertisers as we're

00:24:11.560 --> 00:24:14.780
rolling this pilot out.

00:24:14.780 --> 00:24:17.630
We're going to expand
the coverage of this.

00:24:17.630 --> 00:24:20.260
We're going to get this
in all of your hands,

00:24:20.260 --> 00:24:21.930
really, in the next
couple of months.

00:24:21.930 --> 00:24:25.290
So keep an eye on this
as we roll it out.

00:24:25.290 --> 00:24:28.025
YouTube has been another
phenomenal channel

00:24:28.025 --> 00:24:28.775
for app promotion.

00:24:31.559 --> 00:24:33.350
We started working with
our YouTube friends

00:24:33.350 --> 00:24:35.790
a lot more closely
on this last year,

00:24:35.790 --> 00:24:37.710
and we really brought
some of these ads

00:24:37.710 --> 00:24:40.560
to life around the
middle of 2014.

00:24:40.560 --> 00:24:43.790
It's still early days for
app promotion on YouTube,

00:24:43.790 --> 00:24:46.490
but the results, as far as
our advertisers are concerned,

00:24:46.490 --> 00:24:47.830
have been phenomenal.

00:24:47.830 --> 00:24:49.960
The engagement is
incredibly rich.

00:24:49.960 --> 00:24:54.610
The amount of eyeballs and users
they intersect with on YouTube

00:24:54.610 --> 00:24:56.600
is massive.

00:24:56.600 --> 00:25:00.595
And I think this next quote
really sums it up best.

00:25:00.595 --> 00:25:02.840
So Deepak is a good
friend of ours,

00:25:02.840 --> 00:25:05.380
and he's the Chief Revenue
Officer at Machine Zone.

00:25:05.380 --> 00:25:09.650
Machine Zone is one of
the largest mobile games,

00:25:09.650 --> 00:25:12.340
from a user and revenue
perspective, in the world.

00:25:12.340 --> 00:25:16.470
And if Deepak knows
anything, Deepak really

00:25:16.470 --> 00:25:20.320
knows how to acquire users and
how to acquire them at scale.

00:25:20.320 --> 00:25:22.320
And any of you who've
done this, or who've

00:25:22.320 --> 00:25:24.070
done it for a large
audience, know

00:25:24.070 --> 00:25:26.300
that you need to really
embrace all of the channels

00:25:26.300 --> 00:25:27.770
that you have.

00:25:27.770 --> 00:25:29.750
And Machine Zone and
Deepak really do that.

00:25:29.750 --> 00:25:33.170
They have tried just about
all of the channels that

00:25:33.170 --> 00:25:34.360
are out there.

00:25:34.360 --> 00:25:36.550
So to hear this
feedback from him,

00:25:36.550 --> 00:25:41.880
the YouTube provides users that
are 15% more valuable than he

00:25:41.880 --> 00:25:44.490
can get from any
other video platform,

00:25:44.490 --> 00:25:46.620
to me says a hell of a lot.

00:25:46.620 --> 00:25:49.220
And this is why advertisers
are clamoring more and more

00:25:49.220 --> 00:25:53.070
for access to this
great YouTube inventory.

00:25:53.070 --> 00:25:55.060
We're trying to make
it easy as well.

00:25:55.060 --> 00:25:57.340
Because, as we introduce
all of these new channels--

00:25:57.340 --> 00:25:59.874
Search, Display, YouTube,
Play Store-- the last thing

00:25:59.874 --> 00:26:01.290
you're going to
want to have to do

00:26:01.290 --> 00:26:03.620
is sit there and
hand-craft your campaigns

00:26:03.620 --> 00:26:06.790
to make sure they work for
each and every one of these.

00:26:06.790 --> 00:26:09.952
So our first step in
simplicity and automation

00:26:09.952 --> 00:26:11.660
is what we're showing
on the screen here.

00:26:11.660 --> 00:26:15.210
Earlier this year, we launched
the ability for advertisers

00:26:15.210 --> 00:26:20.010
to extend their existing
AdMob in-app app promotion

00:26:20.010 --> 00:26:23.040
campaigns to the mobile web.

00:26:23.040 --> 00:26:24.470
What we do is we
take all of that

00:26:24.470 --> 00:26:26.442
carefully crafted
targeting criteria

00:26:26.442 --> 00:26:28.390
that you have so
carefully assembled

00:26:28.390 --> 00:26:32.740
for your in-app promotions, and
we take it and we lift that up

00:26:32.740 --> 00:26:34.880
and we drop it over to
the mobile web space.

00:26:34.880 --> 00:26:37.610
So we can find your
users that are roughly as

00:26:37.610 --> 00:26:40.310
valuable at roughly
the same CPI,

00:26:40.310 --> 00:26:44.140
but in the mobile web
rather than in-app.

00:26:44.140 --> 00:26:47.380
And this enables you to find new
unique users that you wouldn't

00:26:47.380 --> 00:26:49.827
have acquired otherwise.

00:26:49.827 --> 00:26:51.660
And advertisers are
seeing stunning results,

00:26:51.660 --> 00:26:52.600
if you ask me.

00:26:52.600 --> 00:26:54.490
Through nothing more
than a checkbox,

00:26:54.490 --> 00:26:56.600
advertisers are
extending their reach

00:26:56.600 --> 00:27:01.720
and are acquiring roughly 30%
more unique users with nothing

00:27:01.720 --> 00:27:04.000
more than that checkbox.

00:27:04.000 --> 00:27:06.060
So as we started to see
the success of this,

00:27:06.060 --> 00:27:09.150
and we thought more and more
about automation at scale,

00:27:09.150 --> 00:27:12.604
we wondered if we could
take this one step further.

00:27:12.604 --> 00:27:14.020
And that's really
where we came up

00:27:14.020 --> 00:27:17.970
with this concept for
universal app campaigns.

00:27:17.970 --> 00:27:21.100
Why stop with the connection
between the AdMob network

00:27:21.100 --> 00:27:22.680
and the mobile web network?

00:27:22.680 --> 00:27:28.190
Why not automate this at scale
for as many advertisers as

00:27:28.190 --> 00:27:29.770
possible?

00:27:29.770 --> 00:27:31.280
Universal app
campaigns, which has

00:27:31.280 --> 00:27:35.120
been in beta and early pilot
for the last couple of quarters

00:27:35.120 --> 00:27:38.980
and is rolling out to all of you
in the next couple of months,

00:27:38.980 --> 00:27:43.250
gives app promoters and app
developers the simplest way

00:27:43.250 --> 00:27:47.170
to acquire valuable
users at scale.

00:27:47.170 --> 00:27:49.582
We're talking about
roughly three inputs

00:27:49.582 --> 00:27:51.290
from the advertiser
or the app developer.

00:27:51.290 --> 00:27:52.889
You got to tell me
what your app is;

00:27:52.889 --> 00:27:54.930
we can go then and find
all the great information

00:27:54.930 --> 00:27:56.570
we need to about your app.

00:27:56.570 --> 00:27:58.250
You got to tell me
how much money you're

00:27:58.250 --> 00:28:00.949
willing to put into the
system, what your budget is.

00:28:00.949 --> 00:28:02.990
And then you have to give
me some characteristics

00:28:02.990 --> 00:28:04.698
about the type of
users you want to find,

00:28:04.698 --> 00:28:07.230
but this isn't heavy-handed
targeting criteria.

00:28:07.230 --> 00:28:09.380
This is like, find
me roughly users

00:28:09.380 --> 00:28:12.690
at this CPI or this
target lifetime value.

00:28:12.690 --> 00:28:14.120
And that's it.

00:28:14.120 --> 00:28:15.422
We do the rest.

00:28:15.422 --> 00:28:16.880
And for those of
you at the keynote

00:28:16.880 --> 00:28:21.080
yesterday, you understand the
power of the machine learning

00:28:21.080 --> 00:28:23.920
technology, the artificial
intelligence and machine

00:28:23.920 --> 00:28:25.916
learning technology,
that we have at Google.

00:28:25.916 --> 00:28:28.290
And we essentially take those
handful of inputs from you,

00:28:28.290 --> 00:28:30.950
and we use our bidding
algorithms, our automation

00:28:30.950 --> 00:28:34.130
algorithms, these massive
machine learning systems,

00:28:34.130 --> 00:28:37.870
to scan across all of these
different networks between Play

00:28:37.870 --> 00:28:41.500
and YouTube and Google
Search and AdMob.

00:28:41.500 --> 00:28:46.030
And we work to find the next
cheapest install, agnostic

00:28:46.030 --> 00:28:48.920
of channel, that satisfies
that goal that you've

00:28:48.920 --> 00:28:50.670
set out for us.

00:28:50.670 --> 00:28:53.150
The results have
been incredible.

00:28:53.150 --> 00:28:56.160
Advertisers have to do very,
very little effort here

00:28:56.160 --> 00:28:59.570
and are finding that this
scales much, much better

00:28:59.570 --> 00:29:01.720
than individual campaigns.

00:29:01.720 --> 00:29:04.390
Because they're able
to find-- the best

00:29:04.390 --> 00:29:06.870
way to think about this is,
we can acquire a set of users

00:29:06.870 --> 00:29:11.250
for you very, very cheaply on
the search side of the world.

00:29:11.250 --> 00:29:13.490
I think about when
those navigational type

00:29:13.490 --> 00:29:14.470
queries come in.

00:29:14.470 --> 00:29:18.600
That's an exact match; it's
a very low cost per install.

00:29:18.600 --> 00:29:22.420
But then in order to truly
grow your volume in search,

00:29:22.420 --> 00:29:24.830
you may find that you
see a significant step up

00:29:24.830 --> 00:29:28.610
in price from a cost
per install perspective.

00:29:28.610 --> 00:29:32.720
What Universal App campaigns is,
is it helps us spread that out.

00:29:32.720 --> 00:29:35.980
So we might find that next
tranche of cheaper users

00:29:35.980 --> 00:29:38.100
to acquire sits in
the AdMob space,

00:29:38.100 --> 00:29:39.940
or maybe on the Play Store.

00:29:39.940 --> 00:29:41.630
And our bidding
algorithms can work

00:29:41.630 --> 00:29:44.030
across all of these
different properties

00:29:44.030 --> 00:29:47.620
to maximize the number of users
we acquire for you at the least

00:29:47.620 --> 00:29:49.240
cost possible.

00:29:49.240 --> 00:29:52.210
We are incredibly excited
about what we're building here,

00:29:52.210 --> 00:29:54.380
and we hope all of you
in the audience try it.

00:29:57.800 --> 00:30:02.990
One of the things that's really
a benefit to us at Google,

00:30:02.990 --> 00:30:06.020
as we approach this
app promotion space,

00:30:06.020 --> 00:30:10.150
is the fact that, for the
better part of the last 15 years

00:30:10.150 --> 00:30:14.290
or so, we've been working
on ads-targeting technology.

00:30:14.290 --> 00:30:18.870
And we bring all of that
to bear in this apps space.

00:30:18.870 --> 00:30:21.110
I was talking about
our machine learning,

00:30:21.110 --> 00:30:23.872
and the key algorithm that
we use in the ad space

00:30:23.872 --> 00:30:25.580
is something called
Conversion Optimizer.

00:30:28.410 --> 00:30:30.160
Very simply,
Conversion Optimizer

00:30:30.160 --> 00:30:33.040
works to maximize the
number of conversions--

00:30:33.040 --> 00:30:35.810
in this case, installs--
that we can deliver

00:30:35.810 --> 00:30:38.180
to an advertiser,
given a certain price

00:30:38.180 --> 00:30:43.020
or given a target
cost per acquisition.

00:30:43.020 --> 00:30:45.700
For the app space, we've tuned
those conversion optimized

00:30:45.700 --> 00:30:48.760
models to take into account
all kinds of signals

00:30:48.760 --> 00:30:52.450
about our users as they
sit on our platforms.

00:30:52.450 --> 00:30:54.450
So we can do these
kinds of things.

00:30:54.450 --> 00:30:56.900
We can bid higher
for users who we

00:30:56.900 --> 00:30:58.770
believe are more
inclined to make

00:30:58.770 --> 00:31:00.774
an in-app purchase overall.

00:31:00.774 --> 00:31:02.190
So if you're a
game developer, you

00:31:02.190 --> 00:31:04.740
rely on IAP to
make a living, you

00:31:04.740 --> 00:31:09.350
want to find users who are going
to spend money in your app.

00:31:09.350 --> 00:31:12.090
So we start to be able
to identify these,

00:31:12.090 --> 00:31:14.930
and we know they're more
valuable and will bid higher.

00:31:14.930 --> 00:31:16.660
We can go even further, though.

00:31:16.660 --> 00:31:19.510
We can start to predict-- we can
actually do this quite well--

00:31:19.510 --> 00:31:23.010
we can predict the probability
that a particular user,

00:31:23.010 --> 00:31:27.779
an individual user, will
actually purchase in your app.

00:31:27.779 --> 00:31:30.070
I got to tell you-- when I
talk app developers and game

00:31:30.070 --> 00:31:33.910
developers about this
specific technology,

00:31:33.910 --> 00:31:36.550
I mean, their wallets
come out almost instantly.

00:31:36.550 --> 00:31:39.340
It's like, well, if you can
deliver me paying users,

00:31:39.340 --> 00:31:41.520
I'm willing to pay
whatever it takes.

00:31:41.520 --> 00:31:43.800
And this is the core of
what we're focused on when

00:31:43.800 --> 00:31:45.710
we talk about app promotion.

00:31:45.710 --> 00:31:47.850
And we do things
like expanding reach

00:31:47.850 --> 00:31:49.840
as well, if that is helpful.

00:31:49.840 --> 00:31:52.770
We can bid lower, but we can
bring more low-cost users

00:31:52.770 --> 00:31:54.980
in if you want volume.

00:31:54.980 --> 00:31:56.230
The results are extraordinary.

00:31:56.230 --> 00:31:59.300
When we do this right,
campaigns that leverage

00:31:59.300 --> 00:32:03.620
this technology
are 24 times more

00:32:03.620 --> 00:32:08.310
likely to generate a buyer.

00:32:08.310 --> 00:32:15.440
And therefore, the cost of
acquiring a buyer drops by 90%.

00:32:15.440 --> 00:32:18.440
Because, if you're interested
in buyers and only buyers,

00:32:18.440 --> 00:32:20.601
you're wasting a lot of
money bringing non-buyers

00:32:20.601 --> 00:32:21.350
into the equation.

00:32:24.620 --> 00:32:27.222
Acquiring users acquiring
valuable users at scale--

00:32:27.222 --> 00:32:28.930
isn't the only thing
you need to do here.

00:32:28.930 --> 00:32:31.845
You absolutely need to
understand your data.

00:32:31.845 --> 00:32:33.470
You need to understand
the performance,

00:32:33.470 --> 00:32:35.650
you need to understand what's
working and what isn't.

00:32:35.650 --> 00:32:37.470
Because, ultimately,
it's you're were dollars

00:32:37.470 --> 00:32:39.120
that you're paying to
acquire these users,

00:32:39.120 --> 00:32:40.619
and you want to
make sure that those

00:32:40.619 --> 00:32:43.390
are invested the best possible.

00:32:43.390 --> 00:32:46.827
The thing that really
stuns me and my team--

00:32:46.827 --> 00:32:49.160
we've been out talking about
the importance of analytics

00:32:49.160 --> 00:32:52.140
in apps for the better part of
the last four years-- and yet,

00:32:52.140 --> 00:32:56.630
still, our surveys indicate
that only 21% of app developers

00:32:56.630 --> 00:33:01.160
actually use some form
of analytic solution.

00:33:01.160 --> 00:33:06.670
I have no idea how the
other 79% of app developers

00:33:06.670 --> 00:33:08.390
run their businesses.

00:33:08.390 --> 00:33:11.650
So we really implore you
to use an analytic solution

00:33:11.650 --> 00:33:14.107
of some kind.

00:33:14.107 --> 00:33:15.940
And I'm going to spend
a few minutes talking

00:33:15.940 --> 00:33:18.180
about our analytic solution
for this, which is Google

00:33:18.180 --> 00:33:19.940
Analytics for mobile apps.

00:33:19.940 --> 00:33:23.210
Now, Google Analytics has been
working on mobile app solutions

00:33:23.210 --> 00:33:26.880
for the last two to three
years, and they're really,

00:33:26.880 --> 00:33:29.900
really becoming quite robust.

00:33:29.900 --> 00:33:32.980
On the buy side now,
Google Analytics

00:33:32.980 --> 00:33:38.370
gives you access to all of these
core app-user-based concepts--

00:33:38.370 --> 00:33:41.450
things like lifetime
value reporting.

00:33:41.450 --> 00:33:47.050
In this example, you understand
the value of users in aggregate

00:33:47.050 --> 00:33:49.810
as they spend a longer and
longer time on your app.

00:33:49.810 --> 00:33:52.400
And eventually it asymptotes
to roughly lifetime value here

00:33:52.400 --> 00:33:58.340
of about $9, but you also see
how that increases over time.

00:33:58.340 --> 00:34:00.140
Cohort analysis is
pretty interesting,

00:34:00.140 --> 00:34:03.100
because it breaks
this down by days.

00:34:03.100 --> 00:34:04.780
A lot of larger
app developers are

00:34:04.780 --> 00:34:08.320
starting to do things like run
TV ad campaigns in conjunction

00:34:08.320 --> 00:34:10.540
with what they're doing online.

00:34:10.540 --> 00:34:12.310
And that's an
example you see here

00:34:12.310 --> 00:34:15.530
where there might have been a TV
campaign run on the February 4

00:34:15.530 --> 00:34:19.120
date, which is what's
driving higher retention.

00:34:19.120 --> 00:34:21.409
You need to understand
how external events might

00:34:21.409 --> 00:34:23.575
be changing the types of
users that you're acquiring

00:34:23.575 --> 00:34:29.210
and might be changing how those
users engage with your app.

00:34:29.210 --> 00:34:31.280
ARPU, of course
is a key concept--

00:34:31.280 --> 00:34:33.420
sorry, average
revenue-per-user, or ARPU,

00:34:33.420 --> 00:34:36.501
is a key concept to most app
developers care an awful lot

00:34:36.501 --> 00:34:37.000
about.

00:34:37.000 --> 00:34:42.370
I want to know how much
value each user's driving

00:34:42.370 --> 00:34:44.520
in aggregate.

00:34:44.520 --> 00:34:47.340
It also helps you think about
how you should be targeting

00:34:47.340 --> 00:34:49.389
your cost per install,
because in order

00:34:49.389 --> 00:34:51.550
to get a positive ROI
back out of the system,

00:34:51.550 --> 00:34:54.060
you can't be paying more to
acquire users than they're

00:34:54.060 --> 00:34:55.170
driving back to you.

00:34:59.590 --> 00:35:02.550
Jason Titus made a number
of announcements on stage

00:35:02.550 --> 00:35:06.120
yesterday about our approach
in this mobile analytics world,

00:35:06.120 --> 00:35:07.920
and I want to reinforce
those right now.

00:35:10.960 --> 00:35:14.730
Our analytics team
understands how important

00:35:14.730 --> 00:35:18.570
it is that they remain neutral.

00:35:18.570 --> 00:35:20.580
And one of the key
ways to enable that,

00:35:20.580 --> 00:35:24.080
and to show you that we're
really trying to be neutral

00:35:24.080 --> 00:35:28.160
and to be agnostic to the media
you buy or the media you track

00:35:28.160 --> 00:35:32.320
or the tools you use,
is we're continuing

00:35:32.320 --> 00:35:36.790
to pursue an incredibly
transparent, open, and reliable

00:35:36.790 --> 00:35:38.930
approach to mobile analytics.

00:35:38.930 --> 00:35:42.390
And we are committed to this.

00:35:42.390 --> 00:35:46.530
We are incredibly
committed to this.

00:35:46.530 --> 00:35:50.830
Our mobile app analytics
tools-- Google Analytics now

00:35:50.830 --> 00:35:55.960
supports iOS conversion tracking
across over 20 ad networks

00:35:55.960 --> 00:35:57.810
that you see behind me here.

00:35:57.810 --> 00:35:59.640
So Google Analytics
integrates, not

00:35:59.640 --> 00:36:02.260
just with networks like
the Google Search network

00:36:02.260 --> 00:36:05.110
or Google Search
or AdMob, but also

00:36:05.110 --> 00:36:06.820
all of these networks on iOS.

00:36:06.820 --> 00:36:09.260
And we integrate with a
number of these networks

00:36:09.260 --> 00:36:11.560
on the Android side as well.

00:36:11.560 --> 00:36:13.750
We've got to stay open,
we've got to say flexible,

00:36:13.750 --> 00:36:17.140
and we've got to be as
transparent as possible

00:36:17.140 --> 00:36:19.190
to continue to grow
this vibrant ecosystem.

00:36:21.910 --> 00:36:25.730
Many of you who care about
tracking installs and value

00:36:25.730 --> 00:36:27.760
across a variety of
different networks

00:36:27.760 --> 00:36:31.030
use third-party
measurement partners.

00:36:31.030 --> 00:36:33.400
These are good friends of
ours, like the folks at Tune

00:36:33.400 --> 00:36:36.180
and Kochava as well as Adjust.

00:36:36.180 --> 00:36:39.060
We've been working very, very
closely with all these folks

00:36:39.060 --> 00:36:41.080
and more to make
sure that you can

00:36:41.080 --> 00:36:44.360
use these third-party
tools as reliably as you

00:36:44.360 --> 00:36:48.250
would use Google Analytics.

00:36:48.250 --> 00:36:52.870
You can now integrate your
third-party measurement tools

00:36:52.870 --> 00:36:56.930
tracking and reports
directly into AdWords.

00:36:56.930 --> 00:36:59.490
And our teams have been working
with the brilliant teams

00:36:59.490 --> 00:37:02.340
at these companies for
the past couple of months

00:37:02.340 --> 00:37:06.420
to make sure that the data
that's being pumped in

00:37:06.420 --> 00:37:08.740
is as robust and
reliable as possible.

00:37:13.570 --> 00:37:21.480
To summarize, you've got to
think about all of the ways

00:37:21.480 --> 00:37:24.194
that you can get users
to engage with your app,

00:37:24.194 --> 00:37:25.360
that you can get discovered.

00:37:25.360 --> 00:37:28.480
Because remember-- there
are so many apps out there,

00:37:28.480 --> 00:37:31.490
and it is so hard to
rise above the noise.

